WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.200
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel,

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:22.280
Min Qabnu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan,

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:27.560
Inna Allatheena Kafuroo Bi Ayat Allahi Lahum Azaabuhu Shadeed,

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:31.440
Wa Allahu Azizun Zuntiqan,

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:36.420
Inna Allaha La Yakhda Alayhi Shajijin Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama,

00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:38.820
Assalamu Alaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuhu

00:00:40.220 --> 00:00:43.100
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Rabbil Alameen,

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:46.860
Wa bihi Nasta'een Wa Nusalli Wa Nusallimu Ala Afdali Al-Khalqi Ajmaeen,

00:00:46.860 --> 00:00:50.500
Nabi'ina Muhammadin Wa Ala Alihi Wa Sahbihi Wa Al-Tabi'ina,

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:53.220
Wa Man Tabi'ahum Bi Ihsanin Ila Yawm Al-Din Wa Ba'a,

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:57.700
We commence as always by praising Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:02.580
Nourisher, Cherisher, Sustainer, Provider, Protector, Curer of one and all,

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:07.860
and we send complete blessings and salutations upon Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:01:07.860 --> 00:01:12.420
upon all the messengers whom Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had sent down to man,

00:01:12.420 --> 00:01:15.060
from the very beginning right to the very end,

00:01:15.060 --> 00:01:20.580
and we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to bless all the companions of Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:25.700
those who struggled and strived in order to protect the Deen,

00:01:25.700 --> 00:01:29.860
to look after it, to convey it in such a way that today it has got to us.

00:01:29.860 --> 00:01:32.580
May Allah make us from amongst those who can preserve it

00:01:32.580 --> 00:01:37.540
and realize how fortunate we are to be from amongst the Ummah of Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:44.100
If you take a look at the persecution of the people who had accepted Islam in the early stages,

00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:47.860
if you ask yourself a question as we did yesterday,

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:52.260
why did they accept this faith? Was it because they found wealth there?

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:56.260
No. Was it because they found status there?

00:01:56.260 --> 00:01:59.860
No. Was it because they found something material there?

00:01:59.860 --> 00:02:01.700
No. Was somebody forcing them?

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:05.940
No. Did anyone put a sword at their necks and tell them believe?

00:02:05.940 --> 00:02:11.460
No. So they accepted Islam purely out of faith and conviction.

00:02:12.180 --> 00:02:15.060
Nobody accepted Islam being forced.

00:02:15.060 --> 00:02:19.780
In fact, those who wanted to accept Islam in a lot of the cases

00:02:19.780 --> 00:02:23.700
thought about it so deeply before they actually accepted

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:28.420
because they knew the type of persecution they were going to face

00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:30.580
the minute they uttered the Shahadah,

00:02:30.580 --> 00:02:32.820
I bear witness that there is no god but Allah

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:36.180
and I bear witness that Muhammad is His servant and His Messenger.

00:02:36.180 --> 00:02:39.620
Take a look at Mus'ab ibn Umayr, may Allah be pleased with him.

00:02:39.620 --> 00:02:42.580
He was from a very, very wealthy family.

00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:48.660
He was very spoiled by his parents to the degree that Rasulullah Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam says,

00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:55.460
I did not know a person who was more spoiled by his mother than Mus'ab.

00:02:55.460 --> 00:02:59.700
Mus'ab had clothes which were so well laid.

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.700
He was dressed very well.

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:03.780
He was smelt before he was seen.

00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:05.940
They knew this man and his itr.

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:08.660
So before you could see the man, you would smell him.

00:03:08.660 --> 00:03:12.740
He was from a very wealthy family, MashaAllah, looked after and spoiled.

00:03:12.740 --> 00:03:15.940
When he heard the message of Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:17.220
he accepted it.

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:20.900
When he accepted it, he kept it quiet so his family doesn't know,

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:22.340
from a very powerful family.

00:03:23.060 --> 00:03:26.260
And one day, one person saw him reading Salah

00:03:26.260 --> 00:03:27.540
and they went and told his mother,

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:30.020
do you know what, this man is fulfilling prayers

00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:33.860
according to the manner prescribed or taught by Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.140
And immediately, all hell broke loose.

00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:42.420
She went to him, she spoke to him, she threatened him.

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.060
He obviously did not deny the fact.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:48.020
So he was grounded to the home.

00:03:48.900 --> 00:03:51.060
Everything was taken away from him.

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:54.100
Nothing spent on him until there came a time

00:03:54.100 --> 00:03:56.980
when he did not have proper clothing to wear.

00:03:57.540 --> 00:04:00.820
And when his skin, after it had been so soft

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:05.060
and well looked after, it had started flaking off.

00:04:05.060 --> 00:04:07.140
And still, to him, that meant nothing.

00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:10.100
He was so happy that he had had guidance.

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:13.380
How many of us, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us,

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:15.300
are ready to sacrifice for our deen?

00:04:16.340 --> 00:04:17.380
We have it on the plate.

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:20.820
No one is holding a sword at our necks.

00:04:21.460 --> 00:04:24.020
And no one ever holds swords at our necks.

00:04:24.020 --> 00:04:25.940
We have this on our plate,

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:28.260
but still we find it difficult to adopt

00:04:28.260 --> 00:04:30.820
what Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam had brought

00:04:30.820 --> 00:04:34.420
when it comes to some of the smaller items within our lives

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:37.700
or sometimes there are major things within our lives

00:04:37.700 --> 00:04:39.460
that we refuse to surrender to.

00:04:39.460 --> 00:04:41.300
For example, the laws of inheritance.

00:04:41.300 --> 00:04:43.700
Many people, no matter how wealthy they are,

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:47.940
they tend to forget about what Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam said

00:04:47.940 --> 00:04:49.620
when it comes to the laws of inheritance,

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:51.620
the treatment of women, for example.

00:04:51.620 --> 00:04:54.100
When it comes to various other matters

00:04:54.100 --> 00:04:55.940
that don't suit us sometimes,

00:04:55.940 --> 00:04:57.380
we tend to just throw it away.

00:04:57.380 --> 00:04:59.780
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us from those

00:04:59.780 --> 00:05:01.140
who understand and realize.

00:05:01.140 --> 00:05:03.380
So this is the example of Mus'ab ibn Umayr.

00:05:03.380 --> 00:05:04.500
If you look at his life,

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:06.260
you will find something amazing.

00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:09.620
He was one of those who took part in the battles.

00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:12.180
He had gone to Habasha.

00:05:12.180 --> 00:05:13.540
Habasha is Abyssinia.

00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:15.300
When Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:05:15.300 --> 00:05:17.380
instructed that a little bit later on

00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:19.300
because of the persecutions.

00:05:19.300 --> 00:05:21.460
And he took part in the Battle of Uhud.

00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:23.540
And he was martyred in the Battle of Uhud

00:05:23.540 --> 00:05:25.540
to the degree that when he passed away,

00:05:25.540 --> 00:05:26.820
they were burying him.

00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:29.220
If they covered his feet, his face was showing.

00:05:29.220 --> 00:05:31.380
If they covered his face, his feet was showing.

00:05:31.380 --> 00:05:33.780
He didn't even have enough to cover himself.

00:05:33.780 --> 00:05:36.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:39.620
Then when the verses were revealed as we had said,

00:05:39.620 --> 00:05:47.140
فَصْدَعْ بِمَا تُؤْمَرُ وَأَعْرِضْ عَنِي الْمُشْرِكِينَ

00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:50.340
Proclaim that which you have been instructed.

00:05:50.340 --> 00:05:53.140
And turn away from the Mushriks.

00:05:53.140 --> 00:05:55.220
These polytheists, turn away from them.

00:05:55.220 --> 00:05:56.180
Don't fight them.

00:05:56.180 --> 00:05:57.460
Don't retaliate.

00:05:57.460 --> 00:06:01.620
So the instruction that Allah gave his messenger was

00:06:01.620 --> 00:06:04.660
you proclaim the message but do not retaliate.

00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:08.340
If someone attacks you, remain silent.

00:06:08.340 --> 00:06:09.620
Don't retaliate.

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:10.900
Don't respond.

00:06:10.900 --> 00:06:11.700
Be calm.

00:06:11.700 --> 00:06:14.100
There was a reason why Allah had said this.

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:16.900
In fact, not one reason but many reasons.

00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:18.180
The wisdom was Allah's.

00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:21.700
For us, was just adoption of the law of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:24.180
People understand, some people don't understand.

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:25.940
Whether you understand or not,

00:06:25.940 --> 00:06:28.980
success lies in adopting the law and the command.

00:06:28.980 --> 00:06:31.860
Sometimes with us we say, why is this the case?

00:06:31.860 --> 00:06:33.540
It's good to ask, mashaAllah.

00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:35.620
But whether then you understand it or not,

00:06:35.620 --> 00:06:38.980
you must realize what is compulsory will remain compulsory.

00:06:38.980 --> 00:06:41.220
What is prohibited will remain prohibited.

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:44.580
Whether you understand it or not, subhanallah.

00:06:44.580 --> 00:06:46.660
Because with our small brains and minds,

00:06:46.660 --> 00:06:49.940
sometimes we would not understand the bigger picture

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:53.060
and we won't understand the wisdom of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:54.420
when he instructs something.

00:06:54.420 --> 00:06:56.900
So Allah says to Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:59.220
proclaim the message and don't retaliate.

00:06:59.220 --> 00:06:59.860
Don't respond.

00:07:00.740 --> 00:07:03.220
So now Quraysh was called

00:07:03.220 --> 00:07:04.500
and they were given the message.

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:06.420
They were told one by one.

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:08.260
And Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:07:08.260 --> 00:07:11.220
began attending the festivals of the kuffar.

00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:12.980
He would go to the Ka'ba

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:17.780
and there they had a habit of people making tawaf naked.

00:07:17.780 --> 00:07:19.540
Men and women, absolutely naked.

00:07:19.540 --> 00:07:22.420
Because foolishly they would promise their gods

00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:25.620
that if this happens to us, we will do this.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:28.900
And if we do this, we want that to happen to us and so on.

00:07:28.900 --> 00:07:30.100
So what would happen?

00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:32.020
They would go around the Ka'ba naked.

00:07:32.020 --> 00:07:34.420
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam would go there

00:07:34.420 --> 00:07:35.620
and he would look down and say,

00:07:35.620 --> 00:07:39.780
ayyuhannas qulu la ilaha illallah tuflihu

00:07:39.780 --> 00:07:44.180
O people, say there is none worthy of worship besides Allah,

00:07:44.180 --> 00:07:45.940
besides the maker, the one who made you,

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:49.300
whoever made you, he is the only one worthy of worship.

00:07:49.300 --> 00:07:50.980
Whoever you are going to return to,

00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:53.220
he is the only one worthy of worship.

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:55.460
Utter those words and you will succeed.

00:07:55.460 --> 00:07:56.500
Subhanallah.

00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:57.940
And he continued saying that.

00:07:58.660 --> 00:08:00.420
He was not bothered or interested

00:08:01.140 --> 00:08:03.460
in how they were dressed or not dressed.

00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:06.260
He wanted the message to get to them

00:08:06.260 --> 00:08:09.460
as per the instruction of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:08:09.460 --> 00:08:10.740
He did not intermingle.

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:13.060
Obviously, he did not intermingle.

00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:13.940
They were naked.

00:08:13.940 --> 00:08:17.140
He looked down and he continued delivering the message.

00:08:17.140 --> 00:08:18.580
But the fact that they were naked

00:08:18.580 --> 00:08:20.740
did not stop him from delivering the message.

00:08:20.740 --> 00:08:24.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding.

00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:26.660
When it comes to delivering the message,

00:08:26.660 --> 00:08:29.300
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala help us learn a lesson

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:30.740
from what had happened at that time.

00:08:31.780 --> 00:08:34.500
So here, Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasalam

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:36.580
faced persecution of Quraish.

00:08:36.580 --> 00:08:38.020
They wanted to beat him up.

00:08:38.020 --> 00:08:39.700
You've got the audacity to come

00:08:39.700 --> 00:08:41.860
in our own midst, our territory.

00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:45.140
And you want to come and talk about our gods and our idols.

00:08:45.140 --> 00:08:48.340
And he did not used to swear the idols, not at all.

00:08:48.340 --> 00:08:50.100
But all he used to do is say,

00:08:50.100 --> 00:08:52.900
these idols will not harm, they will not benefit.

00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:56.020
You know, if you look at one of the slave girls,

00:08:56.020 --> 00:08:57.780
her name was Zinnirah.

00:08:57.860 --> 00:09:01.060
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala be pleased with her.

00:09:01.060 --> 00:09:03.620
She accepted Islam, she was a slave girl.

00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:06.740
And Abu Jahl and the likes began to punish her.

00:09:06.740 --> 00:09:08.420
They punished her, they beat her up

00:09:08.420 --> 00:09:11.060
because obviously she was a Roman girl.

00:09:11.060 --> 00:09:14.340
Allahu Akbar had come from the Roman Empire.

00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:15.700
She was enslaved.

00:09:15.700 --> 00:09:17.860
And when they beat her up so much,

00:09:17.860 --> 00:09:21.140
she continued reiterating that she believes in one god,

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:22.980
not in Allat wa al-Uzza.

00:09:22.980 --> 00:09:25.060
Allat wa al-Uzza were names of these idols.

00:09:25.700 --> 00:09:29.300
And they beat her so much that she went blind.

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:33.460
And what had happened is they started mocking

00:09:33.460 --> 00:09:36.340
until Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu came forth

00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:38.580
with some wealth and he purchased her

00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:41.540
and he freed her for the sake of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:44.980
So when she was leaving, they started commenting.

00:09:44.980 --> 00:09:47.780
They said, it is Allat wa al-Uzza

00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:51.940
through whom your sight has been taken away

00:09:51.940 --> 00:09:54.340
because you went against our idols.

00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:57.140
The idols have taken away your sight.

00:09:57.140 --> 00:09:59.300
At that juncture, she said,

00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:02.420
Wallahi, Allat and al-Uzza,

00:10:02.420 --> 00:10:04.500
they can neither harm nor benefit,

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:06.020
neither me nor themselves.

00:10:06.660 --> 00:10:11.140
My eyesight went because of Allah's decision

00:10:11.140 --> 00:10:14.580
and He is the one who will return it to me.

00:10:14.580 --> 00:10:16.740
As she said that, do you know what happened?

00:10:17.940 --> 00:10:19.780
Her eyesight was restored.

00:10:19.780 --> 00:10:23.140
Miracle happened in the midst of Quraysh subhanallah.

00:10:23.140 --> 00:10:24.420
They were gobsmacked,

00:10:24.420 --> 00:10:26.740
but it still did not bat their eyelids.

00:10:26.740 --> 00:10:30.900
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant Zinnirah radiallahu anhu

00:10:30.900 --> 00:10:32.500
a lofty rank in Jannah.

00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:34.180
She indeed went through a lot

00:10:34.180 --> 00:10:37.300
and her eyesight was restored miraculously.

00:10:37.300 --> 00:10:40.260
So Quraysh, they began to plan and plot

00:10:40.260 --> 00:10:42.100
against the Muslims.

00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:43.220
They were harming them.

00:10:43.220 --> 00:10:45.380
They didn't want to do business with them.

00:10:45.380 --> 00:10:48.180
And at the same time, they began swearing, mocking.

00:10:48.180 --> 00:10:51.300
Wherever they could, they would beat up people one by one.

00:10:51.380 --> 00:10:53.300
Next thing you hear, that one was beaten up.

00:10:53.300 --> 00:10:54.660
That one was beaten up.

00:10:54.660 --> 00:10:57.780
All across, there was chaos in the sense that

00:10:57.780 --> 00:11:00.100
although they could not openly fight

00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:03.860
because of each person's family, family members.

00:11:03.860 --> 00:11:06.660
You see, their hearts amongst the family members,

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:10.180
they were two or three staunch enemies.

00:11:10.180 --> 00:11:11.540
And then you would have a few people

00:11:11.540 --> 00:11:12.900
whose hearts are softened

00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:14.180
and you would have a few Muslims.

00:11:14.180 --> 00:11:18.180
So the families were made up of various types of people.

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:20.820
It was impossible for them to beat up people

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:23.460
whose family members were ready to stand up for them

00:11:23.460 --> 00:11:25.460
even though they had not been Muslims.

00:11:26.260 --> 00:11:29.140
But because of the bond and the link of blood.

00:11:29.140 --> 00:11:31.300
So with Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:35.460
Abu Jahl, he had a lot of incidents

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:39.220
where he came forth to harm Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:11:39.220 --> 00:11:40.260
And at that stage, remember,

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:42.180
they still used to ask a few questions.

00:11:42.180 --> 00:11:44.980
They used to still talk to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:47.620
and say, okay, tell your God this and tell your God that

00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:49.700
and we want to know this and we want to know that.

00:11:49.700 --> 00:11:52.020
There were four main things

00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:54.580
that the Kuffar of Quraysh had denied

00:11:54.580 --> 00:11:56.660
or they were finding fault in.

00:11:56.660 --> 00:11:59.300
The first was the issue of Wahdaniyya.

00:11:59.300 --> 00:12:02.020
Wahdaniyya meaning Tawheed, the oneness of Allah.

00:12:02.020 --> 00:12:04.260
How can we worship one God

00:12:04.260 --> 00:12:07.140
when we've been worshiping so many Gods all along?

00:12:07.140 --> 00:12:10.020
And this is why they began to call him mad.

00:12:16.020 --> 00:12:19.540
Has he made all the Gods into one God?

00:12:20.180 --> 00:12:21.700
Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:24.020
did not make the Gods into one God.

00:12:24.020 --> 00:12:30.020
No, he told them all these Gods will neither help nor harm.

00:12:30.020 --> 00:12:32.340
You need to worship whoever made you.

00:12:32.340 --> 00:12:34.420
What was so wrong about that message?

00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:37.300
You need to worship whoever you are going to return to,

00:12:37.300 --> 00:12:38.900
the owner of heaven and hell.

00:12:38.900 --> 00:12:40.340
You worship him alone,

00:12:40.340 --> 00:12:42.260
the one whom you are answerable to.

00:12:42.260 --> 00:12:44.260
That is the only one you shall worship.

00:12:44.260 --> 00:12:45.780
That is Islam.

00:12:45.780 --> 00:12:48.100
And this is what Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:12:48.100 --> 00:12:49.380
called them towards.

00:12:49.380 --> 00:12:52.980
We know the term Allah was used by them as well.

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:55.460
Because Allah means the worshiped one.

00:12:55.460 --> 00:12:57.940
And Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala,

00:12:57.940 --> 00:13:02.340
they did not deny that they were created by one supreme deity.

00:13:02.340 --> 00:13:03.620
But at the same time,

00:13:03.620 --> 00:13:06.180
they refused to worship him alone.

00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:08.820
They only worshiped him when they were in serious trouble.

00:13:09.540 --> 00:13:12.020
So now, Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:15.060
being faced with questions about Tawheed.

00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:17.460
In fact, the oneness of Allah

00:13:17.460 --> 00:13:19.380
was something they continued raising.

00:13:19.380 --> 00:13:22.260
If you look at some of the questions

00:13:22.260 --> 00:13:25.060
that they had asked Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:13:25.060 --> 00:13:25.780
they told him,

00:13:29.140 --> 00:13:30.980
you are a magician and you are a liar.

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:32.820
Where is he a liar from?

00:13:32.820 --> 00:13:34.020
What did he lie about?

00:13:34.020 --> 00:13:35.060
He is just telling them,

00:13:35.060 --> 00:13:37.300
look, this won't harm and it won't help.

00:13:38.020 --> 00:13:39.860
So it cannot harm or help itself.

00:13:39.860 --> 00:13:41.300
Why do you call me a liar?

00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:42.420
I'm giving you information.

00:13:42.420 --> 00:13:44.500
Go and try it, test it, see.

00:13:44.500 --> 00:13:46.580
May Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala bless us all.

00:13:47.460 --> 00:13:51.620
They went on a smear campaign, character assassination,

00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:54.580
or what we can call a media campaign.

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:56.900
On its own level, at that particular time,

00:13:56.900 --> 00:13:58.900
they went around Quraysh saying,

00:13:58.900 --> 00:14:00.020
this man is possessed.

00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:01.780
It's confirmed that he's a madman.

00:14:01.780 --> 00:14:04.340
The doctors have come in or the experts have come in.

00:14:04.340 --> 00:14:06.020
They've confirmed this man is possessed.

00:14:06.020 --> 00:14:07.140
He's a madman.

00:14:07.140 --> 00:14:08.980
Or they continue to say,

00:14:08.980 --> 00:14:10.420
he is a fortune teller.

00:14:10.420 --> 00:14:12.740
You see, he's coming to say things of the future.

00:14:13.380 --> 00:14:14.500
And then they also said,

00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:16.980
he's a very, very eloquent poet.

00:14:16.980 --> 00:14:18.900
But what he came with was not poetry.

00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:21.540
They also said, he's mad, possessed,

00:14:21.540 --> 00:14:24.500
and he has within him a jinn.

00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:27.700
Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala protect us.

00:14:27.700 --> 00:14:30.580
They then said someone has done magic on him.

00:14:30.580 --> 00:14:32.340
And at one stage, they even said,

00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:33.860
he's a magician himself.

00:14:33.860 --> 00:14:35.060
Because the magicians,

00:14:35.060 --> 00:14:37.460
they separate between husband and wife.

00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:39.700
And all these accusations,

00:14:39.700 --> 00:14:42.100
all these accusations amounted to nothing

00:14:42.100 --> 00:14:44.660
when it came to Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam.

00:14:44.660 --> 00:14:46.740
Because Allah Subhanahu Wa Ta'ala

00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:48.820
told Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:14:56.260 --> 00:14:58.260
we have protected you

00:14:58.260 --> 00:15:00.660
against those who mock about you.

00:15:01.700 --> 00:15:03.300
So they can mock,

00:15:03.300 --> 00:15:04.900
it will be to their detriment,

00:15:04.900 --> 00:15:05.700
not to yours.

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:07.940
Up to today, that verse is valid.

00:15:08.900 --> 00:15:11.940
Those who want to mock at Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:15:12.580 --> 00:15:14.820
they want to draw cartoons about him.

00:15:14.820 --> 00:15:16.180
They want to make images

00:15:16.180 --> 00:15:18.340
and they want to try and make fools

00:15:18.340 --> 00:15:21.700
of what the messenger's message was and so on.

00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:23.300
Allah says, don't worry.

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:25.620
We have protected you from that.

00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:28.740
You are far higher than all they can do

00:15:28.740 --> 00:15:30.180
when it comes to mocking.

00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:32.420
And it will be against them.

00:15:32.420 --> 00:15:36.660
Did you realize that when the cartoons were drawn lately,

00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:39.060
it resulted in great exposure for Islam

00:15:39.060 --> 00:15:42.260
and the Muslims and so many people turned to Islam.

00:15:42.260 --> 00:15:43.860
For the first time in their lives,

00:15:43.860 --> 00:15:46.580
they found out that it is a religion of purity,

00:15:46.580 --> 00:15:48.580
the purest of all religions.

00:15:48.580 --> 00:15:49.860
And they began to turn.

00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:51.780
Had it not been for those cartoons,

00:15:51.780 --> 00:15:53.780
they probably would have still been lying

00:15:53.780 --> 00:15:54.980
in their ignorance.

00:15:54.980 --> 00:15:56.260
So as we say,

00:15:58.180 --> 00:16:00.100
sometimes something appears negative,

00:16:00.100 --> 00:16:01.540
but there is a lot of positivity

00:16:01.540 --> 00:16:03.380
that comes out of that negative.

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:05.700
Another question they asked,

00:16:05.700 --> 00:16:06.980
the second thing that they asked

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:09.460
about life after death.

00:16:09.460 --> 00:16:10.660
How can you tell us

00:16:10.660 --> 00:16:12.820
that after we are going to be dust,

00:16:12.820 --> 00:16:13.940
we're going to be resurrected?

00:16:14.740 --> 00:16:16.580
As you know in Surah Yaseen as well,

00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:17.860
the question they used to ask,

00:16:22.340 --> 00:16:24.500
who is going to give life to these bones

00:16:24.500 --> 00:16:26.020
after they are dispersed,

00:16:26.020 --> 00:16:28.020
completely decomposed and scattered?

00:16:28.020 --> 00:16:29.540
And Allah responds by saying,

00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:38.020
say to them,

00:16:38.740 --> 00:16:40.340
He will give them life.

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:42.260
Who gave them life in the first place?

00:16:42.260 --> 00:16:44.100
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:44.100 --> 00:16:46.180
help us the day He resurrects us.

00:16:46.180 --> 00:16:47.620
And may we be from amongst those

00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:50.820
who are conscious in our day-to-day lives

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.020
as to our deeds

00:16:52.020 --> 00:16:54.740
so that we can face Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:54.740 --> 00:16:55.780
and through His mercy

00:16:55.780 --> 00:16:58.020
we can attain Jannah and Paradise.

00:16:58.900 --> 00:16:59.780
They also,

00:16:59.780 --> 00:17:01.620
the third thing that they found fault in

00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:03.060
was the messenger himself.

00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:04.020
Who are you?

00:17:04.020 --> 00:17:05.220
You were an orphan.

00:17:05.220 --> 00:17:06.740
You were brought up an orphan.

00:17:06.740 --> 00:17:08.500
You didn't even have a father.

00:17:08.500 --> 00:17:10.660
And later on your mother also died.

00:17:10.660 --> 00:17:11.940
And who are you?

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:14.020
How can you have been chosen by Allah?

00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:24.500
They said,

00:17:24.500 --> 00:17:26.980
why wasn't this Quran revealed

00:17:26.980 --> 00:17:29.300
to a very, very powerful man

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:31.460
either from Makkah or from Ta'if?

00:17:31.460 --> 00:17:33.060
Why did it have to be you

00:17:33.060 --> 00:17:34.660
who is so weak from amongst us?

00:17:35.780 --> 00:17:36.820
So Allah says,

00:17:36.820 --> 00:17:39.780
we chose whom we want to give the message to.

00:17:39.780 --> 00:17:40.740
Allahu Akbar.

00:17:40.740 --> 00:17:41.780
It doesn't mean

00:17:41.780 --> 00:17:44.260
that you have the choice and decision.

00:17:44.260 --> 00:17:45.780
And then they began to say,

00:17:45.780 --> 00:17:47.940
well, why isn't there an angel?

00:17:53.700 --> 00:17:56.420
Why doesn't he have an angel with him?

00:17:56.420 --> 00:17:57.700
If he's really a messenger,

00:17:57.700 --> 00:17:58.900
he must bring an angel.

00:17:58.900 --> 00:18:00.340
The angel must talk to us.

00:18:00.340 --> 00:18:02.740
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala responds

00:18:02.740 --> 00:18:03.780
and Allah says,

00:18:03.780 --> 00:18:05.060
Subhanallah.

00:18:11.060 --> 00:18:12.340
The question was,

00:18:12.340 --> 00:18:14.420
why didn't an angel come?

00:18:14.420 --> 00:18:15.140
And Allah says,

00:18:20.340 --> 00:18:22.660
had we sent an angel,

00:18:22.660 --> 00:18:23.860
we would have brought him

00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:25.140
in the form of a man.

00:18:25.140 --> 00:18:26.500
And the verse just before that

00:18:26.500 --> 00:18:28.180
or part of the verse says

00:18:28.180 --> 00:18:31.220
that had we sent an angel down,

00:18:34.260 --> 00:18:35.460
the matter between them

00:18:35.460 --> 00:18:37.780
would have been immediately judged,

00:18:37.780 --> 00:18:38.340
decided.

00:18:38.340 --> 00:18:40.660
The punishment would have come automatically.

00:18:40.820 --> 00:18:42.660
When you ask for a sign

00:18:42.660 --> 00:18:44.180
and the sign comes

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:45.540
and then you disbelieve,

00:18:45.540 --> 00:18:46.980
you're asking for disaster.

00:18:46.980 --> 00:18:47.700
Subhanallah.

00:18:47.700 --> 00:18:49.620
So it was Allah's mercy

00:18:49.620 --> 00:18:52.020
that he did not send the angel in person

00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:52.980
because Allah says,

00:18:52.980 --> 00:18:55.380
had we sent it as you wanted it,

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:56.980
we would have then sent the punishment

00:18:56.980 --> 00:18:57.620
together with it

00:18:57.620 --> 00:18:59.460
for anyone who disbelieved thereafter.

00:19:00.580 --> 00:19:02.020
And so many other points

00:19:02.020 --> 00:19:03.380
that they raised against Muhammad

00:19:03.380 --> 00:19:04.740
sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:19:04.740 --> 00:19:05.540
one of them was,

00:19:10.660 --> 00:19:15.060
why is this prophet

00:19:15.060 --> 00:19:16.740
who is claiming to be a prophet

00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:20.100
walking in the market places

00:19:20.100 --> 00:19:22.740
and eating food like all of us?

00:19:22.740 --> 00:19:24.020
He should be someone

00:19:24.020 --> 00:19:24.980
who has an angel

00:19:24.980 --> 00:19:26.420
doing his errands for him.

00:19:26.980 --> 00:19:28.740
And Allah says in response to that,

00:19:41.380 --> 00:19:45.700
every messenger that we sent before him,

00:19:45.700 --> 00:19:47.460
every one of them walked

00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:48.580
in the market places

00:19:48.580 --> 00:19:49.380
and ate food.

00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:50.260
Subhanallah.

00:19:50.260 --> 00:19:51.380
So he is no different.

00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:53.620
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:53.620 --> 00:19:54.500
safeguard us.

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:55.940
So many things they raised.

00:19:55.940 --> 00:19:57.700
Another, the fourth point

00:19:57.700 --> 00:19:58.500
that they raised

00:19:58.500 --> 00:20:00.580
was regarding the Quran itself.

00:20:00.580 --> 00:20:01.460
That this Quran,

00:20:02.020 --> 00:20:03.060
why is it coming down

00:20:03.060 --> 00:20:04.340
in drips and drabs?

00:20:04.340 --> 00:20:05.540
Why is it coming down

00:20:05.540 --> 00:20:06.580
verse by verse?

00:20:06.580 --> 00:20:08.020
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:08.580
responds.

00:20:08.580 --> 00:20:09.460
Do you know what they said?

00:20:10.420 --> 00:20:11.620
Subhanallah.

00:20:23.620 --> 00:20:24.500
They questioned,

00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:26.100
why doesn't this Quran,

00:20:26.100 --> 00:20:27.620
why didn't it come down

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:29.620
all at once like the Torah?

00:20:29.620 --> 00:20:30.740
Musa alayhi salam,

00:20:30.740 --> 00:20:31.860
the prophet Moses went,

00:20:31.860 --> 00:20:32.820
he collected the book,

00:20:32.820 --> 00:20:33.780
he came back.

00:20:33.780 --> 00:20:34.980
So why didn't this book

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:36.340
come down just like that?

00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:37.380
And Allah says,

00:20:37.380 --> 00:20:38.900
because Allah wanted it

00:20:38.900 --> 00:20:40.260
to strengthen your heart.

00:20:40.260 --> 00:20:42.580
It came down bit by bit.

00:20:42.580 --> 00:20:43.940
When an incident occurred,

00:20:43.940 --> 00:20:45.220
a verse would be revealed.

00:20:45.220 --> 00:20:46.740
So nobody would forget it.

00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:47.620
To this day,

00:20:47.620 --> 00:20:48.420
we have verses,

00:20:48.420 --> 00:20:49.380
inshallah, this evening

00:20:49.380 --> 00:20:51.140
we are going to look into some of them

00:20:51.140 --> 00:20:52.580
where something happened

00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:54.100
and verses were revealed.

00:20:54.100 --> 00:20:55.300
And immediately,

00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:56.500
the problem was solved.

00:20:56.500 --> 00:20:57.460
Not only that,

00:20:57.460 --> 00:20:58.580
the verse was remembered

00:20:58.580 --> 00:20:59.540
with a story.

00:20:59.540 --> 00:21:01.220
If I were to tell you a story,

00:21:01.220 --> 00:21:03.460
it is far easier for you to remember

00:21:03.460 --> 00:21:04.980
the moral of it

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:06.500
than if I were to just recite

00:21:06.500 --> 00:21:07.860
rules and regulations for you.

00:21:07.860 --> 00:21:08.660
Subhanallah.

00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:10.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:11.540
grant us a deep understanding.

00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:13.140
So they had raised,

00:21:13.140 --> 00:21:15.060
also they raised a point

00:21:15.060 --> 00:21:16.820
regarding the same Quran.

00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:20.820
Asateerul awaleenak tatabaha

00:21:20.820 --> 00:21:25.860
fiyatum laa alayh bukratan wa aseela

00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:27.700
These are tales of the past

00:21:27.700 --> 00:21:29.460
that have been dictated to him

00:21:29.460 --> 00:21:30.980
by night and by day.

00:21:30.980 --> 00:21:32.420
So he checked them,

00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:33.220
he saw them

00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:35.220
and he noted them down

00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:36.020
and so on.

00:21:36.020 --> 00:21:37.460
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:37.460 --> 00:21:41.060
says elsewhere in the Quran.

00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:47.620
Wama kunta tatlo min qabnihi min kitab

00:21:47.620 --> 00:21:50.420
Wala takhuttu biyameenik

00:21:50.420 --> 00:21:55.060
Ithal narutab al mubatiloon

00:21:55.060 --> 00:21:58.260
You never read a book.

00:21:58.260 --> 00:22:00.180
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:00.180 --> 00:22:02.740
You never could read a book.

00:22:02.740 --> 00:22:03.140
Never.

00:22:03.140 --> 00:22:04.580
Before the Quran came,

00:22:04.580 --> 00:22:06.180
you could never read a book.

00:22:06.260 --> 00:22:07.780
Nor could you write.

00:22:07.780 --> 00:22:09.380
Had that been the case,

00:22:09.380 --> 00:22:11.380
maybe then they could have doubted

00:22:11.380 --> 00:22:12.980
that you got it from others.

00:22:12.980 --> 00:22:14.900
But neither could you read nor write.

00:22:15.540 --> 00:22:16.660
You've never read a book

00:22:16.660 --> 00:22:17.860
nor have you written anything.

00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.940
So how then can they come up

00:22:19.940 --> 00:22:21.220
with these accusations?

00:22:21.220 --> 00:22:22.260
Subhanallah.

00:22:22.260 --> 00:22:23.540
So everything went back

00:22:23.540 --> 00:22:24.580
into their faces.

00:22:24.580 --> 00:22:25.460
Subhanallah.

00:22:25.460 --> 00:22:27.460
And this is why Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:27.460 --> 00:22:28.340
challenges them.

00:22:28.340 --> 00:22:29.140
What does Allah say?

00:22:30.180 --> 00:22:30.740
Allah says,

00:22:32.020 --> 00:22:32.580
Tell them,

00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:34.260
O Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:22:34.260 --> 00:22:34.900
challenge them.

00:22:35.380 --> 00:22:38.660
Lain jtamaatil insu wal jinn

00:22:38.660 --> 00:22:41.460
wa ala ayyatoo bimithli

00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:45.380
haathal qur'ani laa yaatoon bimithli

00:22:45.380 --> 00:22:51.380
wa laukana ba'duhum li ba'din zaheera

00:22:51.380 --> 00:22:54.180
If all mankind and jinkind

00:22:54.180 --> 00:22:55.540
had to get together

00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:57.060
and help one another

00:22:57.060 --> 00:22:58.420
to come up with something

00:22:58.420 --> 00:23:00.020
similar to the Quran,

00:23:00.020 --> 00:23:02.660
they would never ever come up with it.

00:23:02.660 --> 00:23:03.940
Challenge number one.

00:23:04.020 --> 00:23:05.700
So they obviously surrendered

00:23:05.700 --> 00:23:06.340
to the challenge

00:23:06.340 --> 00:23:07.300
because they knew

00:23:07.300 --> 00:23:08.980
that this is not going to happen.

00:23:08.980 --> 00:23:09.620
So Allah says,

00:23:09.620 --> 00:23:10.820
Let's make it easier for you.

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:14.420
Are they saying

00:23:14.420 --> 00:23:15.700
that this is fabricated?

00:23:19.460 --> 00:23:20.260
Tell them,

00:23:20.260 --> 00:23:22.420
Bring about ten surahs

00:23:22.420 --> 00:23:23.780
similar to it.

00:23:23.780 --> 00:23:25.540
Ten chapters similar to it.

00:23:25.540 --> 00:23:27.060
And then let's see what happens.

00:23:27.060 --> 00:23:28.660
Still, they couldn't do anything.

00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:29.300
Then Allah says,

00:23:29.300 --> 00:23:30.500
Okay, we make it easier.

00:23:33.940 --> 00:23:43.060
Let them come up with one surah

00:23:43.060 --> 00:23:44.340
similar to it.

00:23:44.340 --> 00:23:46.340
Still, the challenge was not met.

00:23:47.140 --> 00:23:49.140
Then there was the challenge

00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:51.300
right up to the end of time.

00:23:51.300 --> 00:23:52.260
What was the challenge?

00:23:52.260 --> 00:24:04.900
Let them come up with anything

00:24:04.900 --> 00:24:05.940
similar to it

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:07.140
if they are truthful.

00:24:07.140 --> 00:24:08.580
Even if it means a phrase,

00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:09.380
a few words,

00:24:09.380 --> 00:24:10.580
let them bring it.

00:24:10.580 --> 00:24:11.700
They will find

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.620
always the Quran will be higher.

00:24:13.620 --> 00:24:14.500
They tried

00:24:14.500 --> 00:24:15.620
and they said a few things

00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:16.980
which had no meaning.

00:24:16.980 --> 00:24:18.180
And at the same time,

00:24:18.180 --> 00:24:19.540
they were concentrating more

00:24:19.540 --> 00:24:20.500
on the rhyming.

00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:21.700
Whereas the Quran,

00:24:21.700 --> 00:24:23.060
not all the verses rhyme.

00:24:23.060 --> 00:24:23.940
Did you know

00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:25.540
that the verses that rhyme

00:24:25.540 --> 00:24:26.580
all at once,

00:24:26.580 --> 00:24:28.820
they are connected to one topic.

00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:30.980
The minute the rhyming changes,

00:24:30.980 --> 00:24:32.020
the topic has changed.

00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:33.780
That's the power of the Quran.

00:24:33.780 --> 00:24:34.580
Amazing.

00:24:34.580 --> 00:24:36.180
So most of these verses

00:24:36.180 --> 00:24:37.540
that were short and sharp

00:24:37.540 --> 00:24:39.460
were revealed in Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:24:39.460 --> 00:24:41.060
The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:24:41.060 --> 00:24:42.260
used to read Salah.

00:24:42.260 --> 00:24:43.780
It is reported that Abu Jahl,

00:24:44.580 --> 00:24:45.780
Al-Akhnus ibn Shuraik

00:24:45.780 --> 00:24:46.500
and Abu Sufyan,

00:24:46.500 --> 00:24:48.100
these people had got

00:24:48.100 --> 00:24:49.940
up at night separately.

00:24:49.940 --> 00:24:50.820
And they went to where

00:24:50.900 --> 00:24:52.420
Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:24:52.420 --> 00:24:54.580
was reciting the Quran in Salah.

00:24:54.580 --> 00:24:56.260
And they went to hear him.

00:24:56.260 --> 00:24:57.060
Listen.

00:24:57.060 --> 00:24:58.980
So neither of them

00:24:58.980 --> 00:25:01.860
or not a single one of them

00:25:01.860 --> 00:25:03.940
knew that the other one was also there.

00:25:03.940 --> 00:25:05.380
But they were hiding in the dark,

00:25:05.380 --> 00:25:05.940
listening.

00:25:05.940 --> 00:25:08.260
Oh, they enjoy the recitation.

00:25:08.260 --> 00:25:09.300
Beautiful meaning,

00:25:09.300 --> 00:25:10.260
powerful words.

00:25:10.260 --> 00:25:11.460
Allahu Akbar.

00:25:11.460 --> 00:25:13.300
And as they were going back,

00:25:13.300 --> 00:25:14.660
they bumped into each other.

00:25:14.660 --> 00:25:15.860
What are you doing here?

00:25:15.860 --> 00:25:16.340
The other one says,

00:25:16.340 --> 00:25:17.220
what are you doing here?

00:25:17.780 --> 00:25:18.740
Then the third one says,

00:25:18.740 --> 00:25:20.180
what are both of you doing here?

00:25:20.180 --> 00:25:21.860
Well, what are all three of us doing here?

00:25:22.580 --> 00:25:24.660
Well, they had to own up, isn't it?

00:25:24.660 --> 00:25:26.660
We came to listen to these words.

00:25:26.660 --> 00:25:28.100
Don't you dare come back.

00:25:28.100 --> 00:25:28.740
Let's promise.

00:25:28.740 --> 00:25:29.620
Okay, we promise.

00:25:29.620 --> 00:25:31.140
Next day, same thing happened.

00:25:31.140 --> 00:25:31.940
Allahu Akbar.

00:25:31.940 --> 00:25:32.580
Why?

00:25:32.580 --> 00:25:34.500
The Quran has a pull.

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:36.500
If you have sincerity in your heart,

00:25:36.500 --> 00:25:38.980
even to the smallest degree,

00:25:38.980 --> 00:25:40.100
even the kuffar,

00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:40.740
to be honest,

00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:42.500
there are findings today

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:45.780
that people have experimented where

00:25:45.780 --> 00:25:48.260
when you play the Quran melodiously

00:25:48.260 --> 00:25:49.300
to a baby,

00:25:49.300 --> 00:25:52.580
you find the way the baby reacts to it

00:25:52.580 --> 00:25:54.100
in a very calm way,

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:56.820
the same reaction happens with adults.

00:25:56.820 --> 00:25:59.220
When you play the Quran for them,

00:25:59.220 --> 00:26:02.180
the melody of that Quran is such

00:26:02.180 --> 00:26:04.260
that it soothes the hearts

00:26:04.260 --> 00:26:06.340
and it calms the people

00:26:06.340 --> 00:26:08.420
because this is the word of

00:26:08.420 --> 00:26:10.260
the creator of the same people.

00:26:11.940 --> 00:26:12.980
So these three,

00:26:12.980 --> 00:26:14.420
second day, same thing happened.

00:26:14.420 --> 00:26:15.380
Third day,

00:26:15.380 --> 00:26:17.540
they had to swear big oaths

00:26:17.540 --> 00:26:17.940
to say,

00:26:17.940 --> 00:26:20.740
we're never ever going to come back again

00:26:20.740 --> 00:26:21.300
and after that,

00:26:21.300 --> 00:26:22.180
they didn't come back.

00:26:22.180 --> 00:26:24.100
But that itself is evidence enough.

00:26:24.100 --> 00:26:26.580
Abu Sufyan r.a later on

00:26:26.580 --> 00:26:28.260
makes mention of this and he says,

00:26:28.260 --> 00:26:29.220
this is what happened.

00:26:29.220 --> 00:26:29.940
We are telling you,

00:26:29.940 --> 00:26:30.740
this is what happened.

00:26:30.740 --> 00:26:31.620
Allahu Akbar.

00:26:31.620 --> 00:26:32.500
They knew it.

00:26:32.500 --> 00:26:33.620
They knew that it's the truth.

00:26:33.620 --> 00:26:35.380
This is why Allah reveal verses

00:26:35.380 --> 00:26:36.980
to Muhammad s.a.w.

00:26:38.340 --> 00:26:38.820
He says,

00:26:47.540 --> 00:26:59.620
we know that their utterances

00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:00.500
and accusations

00:27:00.500 --> 00:27:01.620
and whatever they are saying

00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:03.540
by their mouths is hurting you.

00:27:04.340 --> 00:27:06.180
We know that it makes you sad

00:27:06.180 --> 00:27:07.060
what they utter.

00:27:07.060 --> 00:27:08.420
They're uttering so many things,

00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:09.380
spreading rumor,

00:27:09.380 --> 00:27:10.980
but we want you to know

00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:12.500
they do not belie you.

00:27:13.300 --> 00:27:15.620
They are denying out of arrogance.

00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:16.580
That's what it is.

00:27:16.580 --> 00:27:17.620
Deep down in their hearts,

00:27:17.620 --> 00:27:19.460
they know what is right and what is wrong,

00:27:19.460 --> 00:27:21.620
but they are denying out of arrogance.

00:27:21.620 --> 00:27:24.660
That verse comforted Muhammad s.a.w. a lot

00:27:24.660 --> 00:27:27.300
because his duty was to deliver the message

00:27:27.300 --> 00:27:28.420
and then he realized

00:27:28.420 --> 00:27:30.020
the message is being delivered,

00:27:30.020 --> 00:27:31.220
but it's the arrogance.

00:27:31.220 --> 00:27:32.500
This is why we believe,

00:27:36.900 --> 00:27:38.740
Whomsoever Allah has guided,

00:27:38.740 --> 00:27:40.020
they shall be guided.

00:27:40.020 --> 00:27:41.140
And whosoever Allah

00:27:41.140 --> 00:27:42.740
has not written guidance for,

00:27:43.460 --> 00:27:44.260
there is no chance

00:27:44.260 --> 00:27:45.620
that they will be guided

00:27:45.620 --> 00:27:47.620
because guidance is not written for them.

00:27:47.620 --> 00:27:49.060
May Allah s.w.t

00:27:49.060 --> 00:27:50.260
guide us at all times

00:27:50.260 --> 00:27:51.860
and may He make us steadfast.

00:27:51.860 --> 00:27:54.100
So these were the challenges

00:27:54.100 --> 00:27:55.620
that Allah s.w.t

00:27:55.620 --> 00:27:57.860
had given the people of Quraysh

00:27:57.860 --> 00:27:59.140
come up with a little portion

00:27:59.140 --> 00:28:00.180
similar to the Qur'an.

00:28:00.180 --> 00:28:00.980
They couldn't do that.

00:28:02.260 --> 00:28:04.180
I was speaking earlier about Abu Jahl.

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:06.900
He had taken a boulder once

00:28:06.900 --> 00:28:09.940
after having spoken to the chiefs of Quraysh

00:28:09.940 --> 00:28:11.140
in the early days

00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:13.460
just after the call

00:28:13.460 --> 00:28:15.300
became open and apparent

00:28:15.300 --> 00:28:16.020
and he said,

00:28:16.020 --> 00:28:17.620
I am going to kill this young man

00:28:17.620 --> 00:28:19.620
and then Banu Hashim and those people,

00:28:19.620 --> 00:28:20.900
his clan and his family

00:28:20.900 --> 00:28:22.180
can do what they want to me.

00:28:22.180 --> 00:28:23.860
I just want to sort the problem out

00:28:23.860 --> 00:28:26.180
because we're going to lose our power here.

00:28:26.180 --> 00:28:28.580
We are powerful people leading Quraysh

00:28:28.580 --> 00:28:30.820
and we are calling towards these idols

00:28:30.820 --> 00:28:32.740
every year the Arabs are coming around

00:28:32.740 --> 00:28:34.740
and they are worshiping the idols

00:28:34.740 --> 00:28:36.100
and we are going to lose this power

00:28:36.100 --> 00:28:37.860
because He is calling us

00:28:37.860 --> 00:28:39.140
to leave everything

00:28:39.140 --> 00:28:41.300
that we're doing at this moment in time.

00:28:41.300 --> 00:28:43.140
All this worship is a waste of time,

00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:43.860
He is saying,

00:28:43.860 --> 00:28:45.060
worship your maker

00:28:45.060 --> 00:28:46.660
and none other than your maker.

00:28:46.660 --> 00:28:47.860
So if that's the case,

00:28:47.860 --> 00:28:48.740
we're going to lose,

00:28:48.740 --> 00:28:49.620
what should we do?

00:28:49.620 --> 00:28:51.060
Well, I'm going to sort him out.

00:28:51.060 --> 00:28:52.660
So he decided the following day

00:28:52.660 --> 00:28:53.700
he took the boulder

00:28:53.700 --> 00:28:55.460
whilst Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:28:55.460 --> 00:28:56.420
was in sajda,

00:28:56.420 --> 00:28:59.460
he was about to throw that boulder

00:28:59.460 --> 00:29:01.620
on Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:29:01.620 --> 00:29:03.380
from a little bit of a height

00:29:03.380 --> 00:29:04.660
and suddenly he stopped

00:29:05.220 --> 00:29:06.580
and he turned around,

00:29:06.580 --> 00:29:07.220
he went back,

00:29:07.220 --> 00:29:08.260
he put the boulder down

00:29:08.260 --> 00:29:09.460
and the people of Quraysh

00:29:09.460 --> 00:29:10.260
who were watching him

00:29:10.260 --> 00:29:11.220
started laughing at him,

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:12.580
hey, what happened here?

00:29:12.580 --> 00:29:14.900
You the big man of Quraysh here

00:29:15.860 --> 00:29:17.460
and now what has happened here?

00:29:17.460 --> 00:29:18.180
He says, you know,

00:29:18.740 --> 00:29:20.820
when I got near him,

00:29:21.540 --> 00:29:25.860
I suddenly saw a massive camel,

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:28.260
huge camel come in my direction

00:29:28.260 --> 00:29:30.260
and it wanted to eat me up,

00:29:30.260 --> 00:29:30.980
Allahu Akbar,

00:29:30.980 --> 00:29:32.180
and a big man,

00:29:32.180 --> 00:29:33.060
he was so worried,

00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:33.620
so scared,

00:29:33.620 --> 00:29:35.300
he started seeing this camel

00:29:35.300 --> 00:29:36.260
and he says,

00:29:36.260 --> 00:29:37.620
I quickly turned around,

00:29:37.620 --> 00:29:38.580
I put the boulder down

00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:39.380
and I carried on.

00:29:39.380 --> 00:29:40.740
Allah, he doesn't that sound

00:29:40.740 --> 00:29:41.700
like a little baby,

00:29:41.700 --> 00:29:42.900
Allahu Akbar.

00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:45.940
This was Allah protecting his messenger,

00:29:45.940 --> 00:29:47.140
this was Allah,

00:29:47.140 --> 00:29:49.540
this has happened twice to Abu Jahl,

00:29:49.540 --> 00:29:50.660
the ones he was,

00:29:52.260 --> 00:29:53.700
he had oppressed a man,

00:29:54.660 --> 00:29:57.300
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:29:57.300 --> 00:29:59.460
and Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:30:00.900 --> 00:30:01.940
was there,

00:30:02.500 --> 00:30:04.820
the people of Quraysh told this man,

00:30:04.820 --> 00:30:06.500
if Abu Jahl owes you money,

00:30:06.500 --> 00:30:08.500
there's only one way you're going to get it

00:30:08.500 --> 00:30:10.580
and they said this jokingly,

00:30:10.580 --> 00:30:12.020
they wanted to make a mockery

00:30:12.100 --> 00:30:13.940
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:30:13.940 --> 00:30:16.260
they said go to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:30:16.260 --> 00:30:17.860
if he talks to Abu Jahl,

00:30:17.860 --> 00:30:18.900
you'll get your money back.

00:30:19.620 --> 00:30:20.580
Now that was a mockery

00:30:20.580 --> 00:30:22.180
because they knew these two,

00:30:22.180 --> 00:30:25.300
obviously nobody is going to listen to the other here,

00:30:25.300 --> 00:30:28.020
so when this man went to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:30:28.020 --> 00:30:29.380
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:30:29.380 --> 00:30:30.020
told him come,

00:30:30.020 --> 00:30:30.660
let's go,

00:30:30.660 --> 00:30:31.780
he went to Abu Jahl,

00:30:31.780 --> 00:30:32.740
knocked on his door,

00:30:32.740 --> 00:30:34.420
Abu Jahl opened the door

00:30:34.420 --> 00:30:36.260
and when he opened the door,

00:30:36.260 --> 00:30:37.460
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam says,

00:30:37.460 --> 00:30:38.820
you owe this man some money,

00:30:38.820 --> 00:30:39.940
he says yes I do

00:30:39.940 --> 00:30:41.940
and he gave the man his money,

00:30:42.100 --> 00:30:44.020
and the problem was solved.

00:30:44.020 --> 00:30:45.700
So the people of Quraysh,

00:30:45.700 --> 00:30:47.220
they got to hear about it,

00:30:47.220 --> 00:30:48.420
the leaders said Abu Jahl,

00:30:48.420 --> 00:30:48.980
what happened?

00:30:49.540 --> 00:30:51.060
The same thing happened,

00:30:51.060 --> 00:30:53.380
he says when the knock on the door happened,

00:30:53.380 --> 00:30:54.740
I got frightened,

00:30:54.740 --> 00:30:55.940
I came to the door

00:30:55.940 --> 00:30:57.220
and I was so scared

00:30:57.220 --> 00:30:58.180
and when I came there,

00:30:58.180 --> 00:30:59.220
I saw these two people,

00:30:59.220 --> 00:31:00.660
I was asked for the wealth

00:31:00.660 --> 00:31:02.100
and as I was about to answer,

00:31:02.100 --> 00:31:04.740
I saw the same camel come in my direction,

00:31:04.740 --> 00:31:05.540
Allahu Akbar,

00:31:05.540 --> 00:31:07.540
that was the punishment of Allah to Abu Jahl

00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:10.980
and that was also showing Quraysh

00:31:10.980 --> 00:31:13.300
that don't make a mockery of this messenger,

00:31:13.300 --> 00:31:15.780
we have protected him against all mocking.

00:31:15.780 --> 00:31:18.260
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us all.

00:31:19.620 --> 00:31:20.900
So that was Abu Jahl

00:31:20.900 --> 00:31:22.500
and this is what he had done.

00:31:22.500 --> 00:31:24.420
Also if you look at verses of the Qur'an,

00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:26.340
you see the first surah,

00:31:26.340 --> 00:31:28.660
the first verses that were revealed were Iqra,

00:31:28.660 --> 00:31:29.220
we know that.

00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:31.060
If you look further down that surah,

00:31:31.060 --> 00:31:32.820
you will find certain verses

00:31:32.820 --> 00:31:34.180
relating to Abu Jahl.

00:31:34.180 --> 00:31:36.180
If you pick up the English translation

00:31:36.180 --> 00:31:37.620
and read those verses,

00:31:37.620 --> 00:31:39.540
you will find something very interesting.

00:31:40.100 --> 00:31:40.900
Abu Jahl,

00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:43.860
every time he saw Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam praying,

00:31:44.580 --> 00:31:46.420
he would go and stop him,

00:31:46.420 --> 00:31:50.660
and he would physically try and chase him away.

00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:51.620
So what had happened?

00:31:51.620 --> 00:31:52.820
Allah revealed verses

00:31:53.540 --> 00:31:56.820
and these verses were directed to Abu Jahl

00:31:57.700 --> 00:31:59.540
and mentioning his story.

00:32:09.540 --> 00:32:20.180
Right to the end of that surah,

00:32:21.220 --> 00:32:22.420
the verses meaning,

00:32:23.060 --> 00:32:24.260
do you see the one

00:32:24.260 --> 00:32:26.420
who stops the worshipper from praying?

00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:28.420
Do you see the one

00:32:28.420 --> 00:32:30.580
who is stopping the worshipper from praying?

00:32:31.220 --> 00:32:32.420
Does he not see?

00:32:32.420 --> 00:32:34.100
What if he is on the right path?

00:32:35.620 --> 00:32:38.580
What if Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam is correct?

00:32:38.580 --> 00:32:40.180
Then what is this man going to do?

00:32:40.180 --> 00:32:42.100
And what if this man here is totally wrong?

00:32:42.100 --> 00:32:43.220
What's going to happen?

00:32:43.220 --> 00:32:47.220
So why stop a man who is praying to the Almighty?

00:32:47.220 --> 00:32:48.020
For what?

00:32:48.020 --> 00:32:49.060
Why stop him?

00:32:49.060 --> 00:32:52.020
And these verses admonished Abu Jahl

00:32:52.020 --> 00:32:54.660
and warned him of a severe punishment to say,

00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:55.620
you can do what you want,

00:32:55.620 --> 00:32:57.140
you can call all your helpers,

00:32:57.140 --> 00:32:58.260
but on that day,

00:32:58.260 --> 00:33:00.820
we will call the gatekeepers of hell

00:33:00.820 --> 00:33:01.860
and they will take you.

00:33:01.860 --> 00:33:03.620
They will take you from your fall lock.

00:33:03.620 --> 00:33:04.580
You read those verses,

00:33:04.580 --> 00:33:06.340
very powerful verses in the same surah.

00:33:06.340 --> 00:33:08.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:33:08.420 --> 00:33:10.180
Another man, Abu Lahab.

00:33:10.180 --> 00:33:11.460
And we need to know these names,

00:33:11.460 --> 00:33:12.580
the names of the enemies,

00:33:12.580 --> 00:33:14.420
just like we knew the names

00:33:14.420 --> 00:33:16.420
or we learned the names of those

00:33:16.420 --> 00:33:20.100
who had accepted Islam in the early days.

00:33:20.100 --> 00:33:22.020
We will also know who were those

00:33:22.020 --> 00:33:25.220
who harmed Islam and who harmed the messenger

00:33:25.220 --> 00:33:26.740
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:33:26.740 --> 00:33:29.140
Abu Lahab was his uncle

00:33:29.140 --> 00:33:30.660
and he was also a neighbor.

00:33:31.540 --> 00:33:32.340
And every day,

00:33:32.340 --> 00:33:34.660
he used to throw out his rubbish and dirt

00:33:35.780 --> 00:33:37.140
at the door of his neighbor,

00:33:37.140 --> 00:33:38.900
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:33:38.900 --> 00:33:40.500
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:42.820
used to come out and see all the dirt

00:33:42.820 --> 00:33:46.260
and all the bin literally of Abu Lahab

00:33:46.260 --> 00:33:47.060
at his doorstep.

00:33:47.060 --> 00:33:48.260
And he would take it away

00:33:48.260 --> 00:33:49.700
and he would continue saying,

00:33:49.700 --> 00:33:50.980
ayyu jiwarin hadha.

00:33:50.980 --> 00:33:52.740
What kind of a neighbor is this?

00:33:52.740 --> 00:33:53.860
Up to today,

00:33:53.860 --> 00:33:56.100
we as Muslims are not allowed

00:33:56.100 --> 00:33:59.140
to do anything that would harm our neighbor,

00:33:59.140 --> 00:34:01.220
whether he is a Muslim or not.

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:02.980
We are not allowed to do anything.

00:34:02.980 --> 00:34:04.900
So much so that if you want to light

00:34:04.900 --> 00:34:06.420
a fire or a smoke,

00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:07.700
make sure that the smoke

00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:09.620
does not affect them negatively.

00:34:09.620 --> 00:34:10.660
Ensure that.

00:34:10.660 --> 00:34:12.580
Otherwise, we cannot call ourselves

00:34:12.580 --> 00:34:14.180
true followers of this message.

00:34:14.180 --> 00:34:16.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:34:16.500 --> 00:34:17.540
Some people,

00:34:17.540 --> 00:34:18.820
astaghfirullah.

00:34:18.820 --> 00:34:21.780
They disturb the neighbor with so much noise

00:34:21.780 --> 00:34:23.140
every single day.

00:34:23.140 --> 00:34:24.340
And the neighbors,

00:34:24.340 --> 00:34:25.380
if they are not Muslim

00:34:25.380 --> 00:34:26.420
or if they are Muslim,

00:34:26.420 --> 00:34:28.100
did you know they have a right

00:34:28.100 --> 00:34:30.660
for you to ensure the peace

00:34:30.660 --> 00:34:32.900
and the calm within their home.

00:34:32.900 --> 00:34:34.900
They must not be harmed from your noise.

00:34:35.060 --> 00:34:36.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:34:36.820 --> 00:34:37.860
So Abu Lahab,

00:34:37.860 --> 00:34:40.180
he was one of those who did that.

00:34:40.180 --> 00:34:41.380
And you know,

00:34:41.380 --> 00:34:44.740
his wife Ummu Jamil was also a culprit.

00:34:44.740 --> 00:34:47.460
She used to also throw defecation

00:34:47.460 --> 00:34:49.620
at Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:34:49.620 --> 00:34:50.500
literally.

00:34:50.500 --> 00:34:52.820
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:52.820 --> 00:34:54.980
spoke about her in surah Lahab,

00:34:54.980 --> 00:34:56.820
as we heard yesterday.

00:34:56.820 --> 00:34:58.420
May Allah safeguard us.

00:34:58.420 --> 00:35:01.460
These people did nothing good for themselves.

00:35:01.460 --> 00:35:04.420
Because one is to keep quiet

00:35:04.420 --> 00:35:06.100
and to carry on with whatever you are doing.

00:35:06.100 --> 00:35:09.300
But the other is to get up and harm the man.

00:35:09.300 --> 00:35:10.340
Harm the man.

00:35:10.340 --> 00:35:11.620
If you are going to harm him,

00:35:11.620 --> 00:35:14.580
you will really pay for it.

00:35:14.580 --> 00:35:16.660
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:35:16.660 --> 00:35:18.740
Today what happens in our societies,

00:35:18.740 --> 00:35:20.020
we hear of something

00:35:20.020 --> 00:35:21.460
and we don't even know this man

00:35:21.460 --> 00:35:23.060
serves the cause of Allah.

00:35:23.060 --> 00:35:24.580
He has dedicated his life

00:35:24.580 --> 00:35:26.100
to serve the Deen of Allah.

00:35:26.100 --> 00:35:26.900
And what we do?

00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:28.260
We spread rumor about him.

00:35:28.260 --> 00:35:30.100
We spread gossip about him.

00:35:30.100 --> 00:35:31.300
We make his life difficult.

00:35:31.300 --> 00:35:32.660
We cause this and cause that.

00:35:32.660 --> 00:35:34.100
What will happen as a result?

00:35:34.100 --> 00:35:36.180
Do we not think Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:35:36.180 --> 00:35:37.140
will deal with us?

00:35:37.140 --> 00:35:39.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala forgive us.

00:35:39.140 --> 00:35:40.180
May he make us from those

00:35:40.180 --> 00:35:41.860
who are worried about ourselves

00:35:41.860 --> 00:35:42.820
and our deeds.

00:35:42.820 --> 00:35:44.340
And we are worried about our link

00:35:44.340 --> 00:35:45.220
with our maker.

00:35:45.220 --> 00:35:46.740
And if we are worried about others,

00:35:46.740 --> 00:35:48.020
we are meant to be worried

00:35:48.020 --> 00:35:49.380
about our brothers and sisters

00:35:49.380 --> 00:35:50.260
across the globe

00:35:50.260 --> 00:35:51.220
who are suffering.

00:35:51.220 --> 00:35:52.420
And if we can,

00:35:52.420 --> 00:35:54.740
we should do something positive about it.

00:35:54.740 --> 00:35:56.020
But we should never engage

00:35:56.020 --> 00:35:57.060
in something negative.

00:35:57.060 --> 00:35:59.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:35:59.300 --> 00:36:00.580
A very dangerous man,

00:36:00.580 --> 00:36:04.020
his name was Uqbah ibn Abi Muait.

00:36:04.420 --> 00:36:05.700
This man,

00:36:05.700 --> 00:36:08.900
when Abu Jahl called out one day,

00:36:08.900 --> 00:36:10.100
and he said,

00:36:10.100 --> 00:36:12.740
I have the defecation of these camels.

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:13.780
Who is going to throw it

00:36:13.780 --> 00:36:16.180
on Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:36:16.180 --> 00:36:17.620
when he is in sajda?

00:36:17.620 --> 00:36:18.660
Imagine,

00:36:18.660 --> 00:36:20.340
when he is in sajda.

00:36:20.340 --> 00:36:22.180
And Uqbah ibn Abi Muait got up.

00:36:22.180 --> 00:36:23.860
He picked up this thing here.

00:36:23.860 --> 00:36:25.460
And Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:36:25.460 --> 00:36:26.660
was in sajda.

00:36:26.660 --> 00:36:27.620
And literally,

00:36:27.620 --> 00:36:29.060
the defecation of the camel,

00:36:29.060 --> 00:36:31.060
a'udhu billah, Allah safeguard us.

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:32.740
He threw it onto the back

00:36:32.740 --> 00:36:34.980
of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:36:34.980 --> 00:36:36.900
And he remained in sajda.

00:36:36.900 --> 00:36:38.820
The Muslims at the time were weak.

00:36:38.820 --> 00:36:40.820
Nobody could go to remove it.

00:36:40.820 --> 00:36:42.260
Do you know what happened?

00:36:42.260 --> 00:36:44.740
His little daughter Fatima radiallahu anha,

00:36:44.740 --> 00:36:45.940
small little girl,

00:36:45.940 --> 00:36:46.580
what she did,

00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:47.940
she saw her father

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:50.020
in this condition of sujood.

00:36:50.020 --> 00:36:50.900
And she saw that

00:36:50.900 --> 00:36:52.660
he's got all this on his back.

00:36:52.660 --> 00:36:53.780
These people of Makkah

00:36:53.780 --> 00:36:55.220
have really harassed him.

00:36:55.220 --> 00:36:56.260
They have thrown this.

00:36:56.260 --> 00:36:57.380
So she went

00:36:57.380 --> 00:36:59.140
and she took it off his back.

00:36:59.140 --> 00:37:01.620
And she actually wiped it out completely.

00:37:01.620 --> 00:37:03.540
And then he got up from sajda.

00:37:03.540 --> 00:37:06.100
And this is what Uqba ibn Abi Mu'ayyaf did.

00:37:06.100 --> 00:37:08.100
When Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:09.060
got up,

00:37:09.060 --> 00:37:10.180
he says,

00:37:10.180 --> 00:37:13.140
Allahumma alayka bifulan wa fulan.

00:37:13.140 --> 00:37:14.420
Oh Allah,

00:37:14.420 --> 00:37:17.140
I hand so and so over to you.

00:37:17.140 --> 00:37:19.380
I hand so and so over to you.

00:37:19.380 --> 00:37:22.340
And he mentioned names.

00:37:22.340 --> 00:37:23.220
Imagine,

00:37:23.220 --> 00:37:24.980
for the messenger to make a dua.

00:37:24.980 --> 00:37:25.460
Oh Allah,

00:37:25.460 --> 00:37:26.820
I'm handing them over to you.

00:37:26.820 --> 00:37:27.460
Alayka bihim.

00:37:27.460 --> 00:37:27.940
Ya Allah,

00:37:27.940 --> 00:37:29.220
you deal with them.

00:37:29.220 --> 00:37:31.540
What a powerful way of making dua.

00:37:32.260 --> 00:37:34.420
He was executed

00:37:34.420 --> 00:37:35.940
after the battle of Badr.

00:37:35.940 --> 00:37:38.100
He was one of those who was taken captive

00:37:38.100 --> 00:37:39.300
and executed.

00:37:39.300 --> 00:37:40.420
And together with him

00:37:40.420 --> 00:37:41.860
was a friend of his as well.

00:37:41.860 --> 00:37:44.260
Who also harassed Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:37:44.260 --> 00:37:44.820
a lot

00:37:44.820 --> 00:37:47.540
by the name of An-Nadhri ibn al-Harif.

00:37:47.540 --> 00:37:49.300
So we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:37:49.300 --> 00:37:50.340
to safeguard us

00:37:50.340 --> 00:37:52.980
from the dua of his friends against us.

00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:54.420
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:37:54.420 --> 00:37:55.940
protect us at all times.

00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.860
So this Uqba ibn Abi Mu'ayyaf,

00:37:57.860 --> 00:37:59.060
this was one of the ways

00:37:59.060 --> 00:37:59.940
that he had hassled

00:38:00.340 --> 00:38:01.540
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:02.740
He was also a neighbor

00:38:02.740 --> 00:38:04.740
of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:07.700
One day he invited Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:38:07.700 --> 00:38:08.500
to his home

00:38:08.500 --> 00:38:10.100
with the people of Quraysh.

00:38:10.100 --> 00:38:11.940
And Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:38:11.940 --> 00:38:12.980
used to go

00:38:12.980 --> 00:38:14.500
whenever Quraysh invited him

00:38:14.500 --> 00:38:15.860
because he would feel

00:38:15.860 --> 00:38:17.380
maybe they might listen to me,

00:38:17.380 --> 00:38:18.420
maybe they might

00:38:18.420 --> 00:38:19.620
listen to a word or two

00:38:19.620 --> 00:38:21.220
and come onto the right path.

00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:24.340
So when Uqba ibn Abi Mu'ayyaf invited him,

00:38:24.340 --> 00:38:25.780
he went and he entered the house

00:38:25.780 --> 00:38:26.180
and he says,

00:38:26.180 --> 00:38:26.980
Ya Uqba,

00:38:26.980 --> 00:38:27.700
do you know what?

00:38:27.700 --> 00:38:28.900
I'm not going to eat your food

00:38:28.980 --> 00:38:30.180
until you bear witness

00:38:30.180 --> 00:38:31.540
that there is none worthy of worship

00:38:31.540 --> 00:38:32.100
but Allah

00:38:32.100 --> 00:38:33.940
and that I am the messenger of Allah.

00:38:33.940 --> 00:38:36.100
So Uqba ibn Abi Mu'ayyaf looked at him

00:38:36.100 --> 00:38:36.420
and said,

00:38:36.420 --> 00:38:37.380
I bear witness

00:38:37.380 --> 00:38:38.980
that there is none worthy of worship

00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:39.780
but Allah

00:38:39.780 --> 00:38:40.580
and I bear witness

00:38:40.580 --> 00:38:41.940
that you are a messenger.

00:38:41.940 --> 00:38:43.860
So the people of Quraysh later on,

00:38:43.860 --> 00:38:44.420
they said,

00:38:44.420 --> 00:38:46.020
What did you say?

00:38:46.660 --> 00:38:48.100
Did we hear you say

00:38:48.100 --> 00:38:49.300
that you bear witness?

00:38:49.300 --> 00:38:49.860
He said,

00:38:49.860 --> 00:38:50.260
No,

00:38:50.260 --> 00:38:52.180
I had a guest in my house

00:38:52.180 --> 00:38:53.300
who refused to eat

00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:54.660
until I said a few words.

00:38:54.660 --> 00:38:55.460
So I said them,

00:38:56.100 --> 00:38:57.540
I seek refuge in Allah.

00:38:57.540 --> 00:38:59.460
That was the worst statement

00:38:59.460 --> 00:39:00.820
he could have ever uttered

00:39:00.820 --> 00:39:02.020
because there were others

00:39:02.020 --> 00:39:04.340
who were weak and downtrodden in Mecca.

00:39:04.340 --> 00:39:06.420
They never cheated in that way.

00:39:06.420 --> 00:39:07.300
When they uttered it,

00:39:07.300 --> 00:39:08.660
they uttered it powerfully

00:39:08.660 --> 00:39:10.020
with sincerity.

00:39:10.020 --> 00:39:11.620
This man was wealthy.

00:39:11.620 --> 00:39:12.820
He had nothing to lose

00:39:12.820 --> 00:39:13.860
whether he said it or not.

00:39:13.860 --> 00:39:14.580
He could have told him,

00:39:14.580 --> 00:39:16.020
Hey, you can carry on

00:39:16.020 --> 00:39:17.060
but he didn't do that.

00:39:17.060 --> 00:39:18.340
He decided to cheat

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:19.380
and because of that,

00:39:19.380 --> 00:39:20.980
he paid a heavy price.

00:39:20.980 --> 00:39:23.220
One day he was so upset.

00:39:23.220 --> 00:39:24.180
He came to Muhammad

00:39:24.180 --> 00:39:25.460
sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:39:26.100 --> 00:39:27.860
and this was one of the worst things

00:39:27.860 --> 00:39:29.300
that had happened in Mecca

00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:31.380
to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:39:31.380 --> 00:39:32.740
He took a piece of cloth,

00:39:32.740 --> 00:39:34.420
this uqba Ibn Abi Mu'ayd

00:39:34.420 --> 00:39:37.300
and he strangled Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:39:37.300 --> 00:39:39.220
and he kept pulling this cloth

00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:40.900
and Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:39:40.900 --> 00:39:42.420
was choking

00:39:42.420 --> 00:39:44.180
and the only person

00:39:44.180 --> 00:39:45.700
who had rushed to his help

00:39:45.700 --> 00:39:47.700
was Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu.

00:39:48.500 --> 00:39:49.220
And he rushed

00:39:49.220 --> 00:39:51.860
and he wrestled this uqba

00:39:51.860 --> 00:39:54.420
and released Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:39:54.500 --> 00:39:56.180
from that strangled hold

00:39:56.180 --> 00:39:57.540
and he said

00:40:03.780 --> 00:40:05.140
How can you kill a man

00:40:05.140 --> 00:40:05.940
who is saying,

00:40:05.940 --> 00:40:07.140
my Lord is Allah

00:40:08.020 --> 00:40:10.580
and he has brought you clear cut signs

00:40:10.580 --> 00:40:11.540
and you want to kill him.

00:40:11.540 --> 00:40:12.660
Leave him alone at least.

00:40:14.260 --> 00:40:15.380
This was that uqba.

00:40:15.380 --> 00:40:17.300
Another man who really harassed

00:40:17.300 --> 00:40:18.980
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:40:18.980 --> 00:40:21.220
was Al-Aas ibn Wail.

00:40:21.220 --> 00:40:23.380
He was a man who constantly used to pass

00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:24.980
and laugh and joke.

00:40:24.980 --> 00:40:25.860
He used to say,

00:40:25.860 --> 00:40:29.140
these people believe in life after death.

00:40:29.140 --> 00:40:30.580
They say there's going to be heaven

00:40:30.580 --> 00:40:32.660
and everybody's going to get so many nice things

00:40:32.660 --> 00:40:33.780
and there's going to be hell

00:40:33.780 --> 00:40:35.380
and there's going to be this and that.

00:40:35.380 --> 00:40:36.980
So every time he used to pass,

00:40:36.980 --> 00:40:38.260
he used to joke about it

00:40:38.260 --> 00:40:39.060
and he used to say

00:40:46.180 --> 00:40:47.860
Those verses were revealed

00:40:47.860 --> 00:40:49.060
saying the statement

00:40:49.060 --> 00:40:50.900
that this man Al-Aas ibn Wail

00:40:50.900 --> 00:40:51.780
used to utter

00:40:51.780 --> 00:40:53.060
and the people of Quraysh.

00:40:53.060 --> 00:40:53.700
They used to say,

00:40:54.580 --> 00:40:57.700
oh, we are only going to live in this life

00:40:58.420 --> 00:41:01.380
and there is no life after death.

00:41:02.020 --> 00:41:03.460
Whatever will kill us

00:41:03.460 --> 00:41:05.540
or what will actually kill us is time.

00:41:05.540 --> 00:41:07.380
It's only time that makes us old

00:41:07.380 --> 00:41:08.340
and we will die.

00:41:08.340 --> 00:41:09.860
We're not going to be resurrected

00:41:09.860 --> 00:41:10.500
and Allah says

00:41:11.940 --> 00:41:13.220
those are their doubts.

00:41:13.220 --> 00:41:14.340
What do they know?

00:41:14.340 --> 00:41:16.980
But this man crossed a certain limit.

00:41:16.980 --> 00:41:17.780
What was that limit?

00:41:18.900 --> 00:41:21.940
He was owed money by Khabbab ibn al-Arat.

00:41:22.020 --> 00:41:23.620
In fact, he owed money

00:41:23.620 --> 00:41:25.700
to Khabbab ibn al-Arat radiallahu anhu.

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:27.780
Al-Aas ibn Wail owed money

00:41:27.780 --> 00:41:30.180
to Khabbab ibn al-Arat who was a Muslim

00:41:30.180 --> 00:41:31.620
and Khabbab ibn al-Arat

00:41:31.620 --> 00:41:32.820
every time he went to him,

00:41:32.820 --> 00:41:34.820
this man used to duck and die

00:41:34.820 --> 00:41:36.020
because now the Muslims,

00:41:36.020 --> 00:41:36.980
nobody's going to come and say,

00:41:36.980 --> 00:41:38.180
hey, where's this man's money?

00:41:38.740 --> 00:41:41.380
So one day Khabbab ibn al-Arat

00:41:42.260 --> 00:41:43.780
had got hold of a few people

00:41:43.780 --> 00:41:44.820
and they went to this man

00:41:44.820 --> 00:41:45.300
and told him,

00:41:45.300 --> 00:41:45.780
look, you know,

00:41:45.780 --> 00:41:47.780
you need to give him his money.

00:41:48.820 --> 00:41:50.740
So Al-Aas ibn Wail says,

00:41:50.820 --> 00:41:52.420
isn't he one of those

00:41:52.420 --> 00:41:54.740
who believes that there's going to be heaven

00:41:54.740 --> 00:41:57.140
and there's going to be lots of goodness

00:41:57.140 --> 00:41:57.940
and in heaven,

00:41:57.940 --> 00:41:59.700
you get whatever you want and so on?

00:42:00.500 --> 00:42:01.380
So Khabbab says,

00:42:01.380 --> 00:42:03.300
yes, indeed, I believe that

00:42:03.300 --> 00:42:04.100
there will be heaven

00:42:04.100 --> 00:42:05.540
and we get what we want there.

00:42:05.540 --> 00:42:06.180
So he says,

00:42:06.180 --> 00:42:08.180
so give me a little bit of time

00:42:08.180 --> 00:42:09.220
when we get to heaven

00:42:09.220 --> 00:42:10.580
and I get whatever I want,

00:42:10.580 --> 00:42:11.780
then I'll pay you your money.

00:42:12.420 --> 00:42:13.700
Now look at how foolish he is.

00:42:14.420 --> 00:42:15.860
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:42:15.860 --> 00:42:18.020
revealed verses exposing this man.

00:42:20.740 --> 00:42:28.660
...

00:42:28.660 --> 00:42:30.020
Do you see this man

00:42:31.060 --> 00:42:32.980
who has disbelieved in our signs

00:42:32.980 --> 00:42:34.100
and he is saying

00:42:34.100 --> 00:42:35.300
that I am going to be given

00:42:35.300 --> 00:42:36.020
lots of wealth

00:42:36.020 --> 00:42:38.260
and lots of children in paradise

00:42:38.260 --> 00:42:40.900
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala asks a question,

00:42:40.900 --> 00:42:42.820
does he even think

00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:44.580
he's going to go to paradise

00:42:44.580 --> 00:42:46.020
and does he even know

00:42:46.020 --> 00:42:47.780
whether he's going to get anything

00:42:47.780 --> 00:42:48.340
or not?

