00:45:59.140 --> 00:46:00.740
I have heard the Quran

00:46:00.740 --> 00:46:01.380
and you know what?

00:46:01.940 --> 00:46:03.380
It is very powerful.

00:46:03.380 --> 00:46:05.620
It is not the speech of an ordinary man

00:46:05.620 --> 00:46:08.180
nor is it the speech of a fortune teller

00:46:08.180 --> 00:46:10.260
nor is it the speech of a poet

00:46:10.260 --> 00:46:12.420
nor is it the speech of a mad man.

00:46:12.420 --> 00:46:14.420
No, it has a sweetness in it

00:46:14.420 --> 00:46:17.380
and it will have some form of rank

00:46:17.380 --> 00:46:18.740
in the very near future

00:46:18.740 --> 00:46:20.180
because it is very powerful.

00:46:20.180 --> 00:46:22.020
And the people of Quraysh were shocked

00:46:22.020 --> 00:46:24.420
because he was the uncle of Abu Jahl

00:46:24.420 --> 00:46:25.940
and he was one of the leaders.

00:46:25.940 --> 00:46:27.380
They said are you senile?

00:46:27.380 --> 00:46:29.140
This man has now gone mad.

00:46:29.140 --> 00:46:30.980
Abu Jahl decided to go to him

00:46:30.980 --> 00:46:31.780
and spoke to him

00:46:31.780 --> 00:46:34.340
and began to weep and tell him

00:46:34.340 --> 00:46:35.300
how can you say this?

00:46:35.300 --> 00:46:36.500
Come on, a man like you,

00:46:36.500 --> 00:46:37.620
we look up to you,

00:46:37.620 --> 00:46:38.820
we can't lose you,

00:46:38.820 --> 00:46:40.180
we cannot lose you

00:46:40.180 --> 00:46:41.620
to this type of thing.

00:46:41.620 --> 00:46:42.980
And so he got up

00:46:42.980 --> 00:46:44.740
and he walked to the rest of Quraysh

00:46:44.740 --> 00:46:46.980
and he says do you ever think

00:46:46.980 --> 00:46:48.260
Muhammad was mad?

00:46:48.260 --> 00:46:49.220
He was never mad

00:46:50.100 --> 00:46:52.100
and there is no sign of madness in him.

00:46:52.100 --> 00:46:52.980
They were watching him.

00:46:54.180 --> 00:46:55.940
Does he look like he's a fortune teller?

00:46:55.940 --> 00:46:57.220
He's not a fortune teller.

00:46:57.220 --> 00:46:58.500
They were watching him, they shocked.

00:47:00.180 --> 00:47:02.180
Does he look like a person

00:47:02.180 --> 00:47:03.700
who is a magician?

00:47:04.500 --> 00:47:05.940
Does he look like he's a person

00:47:05.940 --> 00:47:08.180
who is this and that, so many things?

00:47:08.180 --> 00:47:10.500
And thereafter, when all of them

00:47:10.500 --> 00:47:12.100
were looking at him quite shocked,

00:47:12.740 --> 00:47:15.220
he then says, well, I think

00:47:15.220 --> 00:47:17.380
we'd rather just call him a magician

00:47:17.380 --> 00:47:19.540
because it's magicians who separate

00:47:19.540 --> 00:47:21.220
between husband and wife

00:47:21.220 --> 00:47:22.260
and family members

00:47:22.260 --> 00:47:23.380
and that's what he has done.

00:47:23.380 --> 00:47:24.580
So they all started laughing.

00:47:25.620 --> 00:47:28.820
Look at how he almost accepted the message

00:47:28.820 --> 00:47:31.700
but because of his colleagues

00:47:31.700 --> 00:47:33.380
and his dignity in society,

00:47:33.380 --> 00:47:34.980
he did not want to accept the message.

00:47:36.740 --> 00:47:38.340
This was Al-Walid ibn al-Mughirah.

00:47:38.340 --> 00:47:40.580
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us all.

00:47:41.140 --> 00:47:42.340
Al-Nadr ibn al-Harith,

00:47:43.460 --> 00:47:44.820
he used to always say,

00:47:44.820 --> 00:47:46.820
I have better speech than Muhammad

00:47:46.820 --> 00:47:47.860
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:47:47.860 --> 00:47:48.660
Come listen to me.

00:47:48.660 --> 00:47:50.020
When the Quran was being read,

00:47:58.660 --> 00:47:59.620
they used to say,

00:47:59.620 --> 00:48:01.380
whilst the Quran was being read,

00:48:01.380 --> 00:48:02.820
make a lot of noise.

00:48:02.820 --> 00:48:04.820
Don't listen, make a lot of noise

00:48:05.460 --> 00:48:07.540
because if you want to overpower

00:48:07.540 --> 00:48:09.300
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:48:09.380 --> 00:48:10.580
don't listen to his message.

00:48:12.340 --> 00:48:13.700
Why did they say that?

00:48:13.700 --> 00:48:15.620
The minute people heard the message,

00:48:15.620 --> 00:48:16.660
they turned.

00:48:16.660 --> 00:48:18.340
They heard a verse, they turned.

00:48:18.340 --> 00:48:20.340
They heard five verses, they turned.

00:48:20.340 --> 00:48:22.180
So they had one option,

00:48:22.180 --> 00:48:24.100
make a noise, ban him.

00:48:24.100 --> 00:48:25.700
Don't allow him to read.

00:48:25.700 --> 00:48:26.260
Stop it.

00:48:26.260 --> 00:48:27.780
We don't want to hear these words.

00:48:28.980 --> 00:48:31.300
And so Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:48:31.300 --> 00:48:32.820
this is what they uttered.

00:48:32.820 --> 00:48:33.860
This man used to say,

00:48:33.860 --> 00:48:35.060
no, no, no, come to me.

00:48:35.060 --> 00:48:36.820
I will give you better stories.

00:48:36.820 --> 00:48:38.660
And he knew a few stories

00:48:38.660 --> 00:48:40.820
of the Persian Empire.

00:48:40.820 --> 00:48:42.260
So he used to come and make mention

00:48:42.260 --> 00:48:43.700
of this Persian leader

00:48:43.700 --> 00:48:44.740
and that Persian leader

00:48:44.740 --> 00:48:46.340
which was nothing like the Quran.

00:48:46.340 --> 00:48:48.100
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:48:48.100 --> 00:48:50.180
protected Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:50.180 --> 00:48:50.820
from this.

00:48:50.820 --> 00:48:52.500
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:48:52.500 --> 00:48:54.180
granted him elevation

00:48:54.180 --> 00:48:56.260
although they were persecuted

00:48:56.260 --> 00:48:57.380
to a great degree.

00:48:58.100 --> 00:49:00.580
Allah blessed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:00.580 --> 00:49:01.220
with an uncle.

00:49:02.180 --> 00:49:04.420
An uncle who was never a Muslim,

00:49:05.060 --> 00:49:06.660
but he was just

00:49:07.300 --> 00:49:09.300
and he had a feeling for his nephew.

00:49:10.260 --> 00:49:11.460
And this is why

00:49:11.460 --> 00:49:14.340
they could not kill Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:14.340 --> 00:49:15.700
because Abu Talib

00:49:15.700 --> 00:49:17.940
who was one of the leaders of Quraysh,

00:49:17.940 --> 00:49:18.820
powerful leader.

00:49:19.540 --> 00:49:21.060
When Abu Jahl and them

00:49:21.060 --> 00:49:23.700
planned to harm Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:23.700 --> 00:49:24.660
he told them,

00:49:24.660 --> 00:49:26.420
you dare touch him.

00:49:26.420 --> 00:49:28.420
If you do, war will break out.

00:49:28.420 --> 00:49:29.220
So now they knew,

00:49:29.220 --> 00:49:30.260
we cannot touch the man.

00:49:30.820 --> 00:49:32.740
And this is why Allah had protected

00:49:32.900 --> 00:49:34.820
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:34.820 --> 00:49:37.220
and the same applies to others who had family.

00:49:37.220 --> 00:49:38.020
They were protected

00:49:38.020 --> 00:49:39.300
because they had family members

00:49:39.300 --> 00:49:41.300
who always stood by them.

00:49:41.300 --> 00:49:42.900
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:49:43.540 --> 00:49:46.180
had granted this Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:46.180 --> 00:49:49.220
this uncle who did not accept the message.

00:49:49.220 --> 00:49:50.820
Quraysh went to the uncle

00:49:50.820 --> 00:49:51.700
and told him,

00:49:51.700 --> 00:49:52.820
talk to your nephew,

00:49:52.820 --> 00:49:54.180
tell him to stop.

00:49:54.180 --> 00:49:56.100
So when he went to the nephew,

00:49:56.100 --> 00:49:56.420
he said,

00:49:56.420 --> 00:49:56.980
look, you know,

00:49:56.980 --> 00:49:58.900
you're putting me in a spot here.

00:49:58.900 --> 00:50:01.860
Quraysh, we know we have got good dealings with them.

00:50:01.860 --> 00:50:03.060
We are related.

00:50:03.060 --> 00:50:04.340
And, you know, now you are,

00:50:04.340 --> 00:50:06.340
you have come with what you have come with.

00:50:06.340 --> 00:50:08.180
Why don't you stop saying all this?

00:50:08.180 --> 00:50:09.780
Because it's about time you stopped.

00:50:10.340 --> 00:50:11.860
He told his uncle wallahi,

00:50:13.460 --> 00:50:16.180
if you were to put the sun in my right hand

00:50:16.180 --> 00:50:17.780
and the moon in my left hand

00:50:17.780 --> 00:50:21.060
and instruct me to stop what I am doing,

00:50:21.060 --> 00:50:22.500
I will not stop it.

00:50:22.500 --> 00:50:24.660
I'm asking them to leave their idols.

00:50:24.660 --> 00:50:25.140
What's wrong?

00:50:26.100 --> 00:50:27.700
This was the persecution.

00:50:27.700 --> 00:50:29.060
So his uncle looked at him and said,

00:50:29.060 --> 00:50:30.020
oh, my nephew,

00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:30.500
carry on.

00:50:30.500 --> 00:50:31.140
Don't worry.

00:50:31.140 --> 00:50:31.540
Carry on.

00:50:31.540 --> 00:50:32.580
You are safe.

00:50:32.580 --> 00:50:33.300
Imagine.

00:50:33.300 --> 00:50:34.180
Meaning deep down,

00:50:34.180 --> 00:50:35.140
he knew what was right.

00:50:35.860 --> 00:50:37.220
He knew what was right.

00:50:37.220 --> 00:50:40.900
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had then,

00:50:42.180 --> 00:50:44.980
meaning blessed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:50:44.980 --> 00:50:46.020
much more.

00:50:46.020 --> 00:50:47.940
He had respect in Quraysh,

00:50:47.940 --> 00:50:49.220
but at the same time,

00:50:49.220 --> 00:50:50.020
hatred.

00:50:50.020 --> 00:50:51.860
They were forced to respect him,

00:50:51.860 --> 00:50:52.740
but deep down,

00:50:52.740 --> 00:50:53.940
they hated him.

00:50:53.940 --> 00:50:55.300
In fact, what they did,

00:50:55.300 --> 00:50:56.980
and this is a very interesting story.

00:50:58.740 --> 00:50:59.620
They got together

00:51:00.180 --> 00:51:00.980
and they decided,

00:51:00.980 --> 00:51:02.580
let's send a man from amongst us,

00:51:02.580 --> 00:51:03.780
an eloquent man.

00:51:03.780 --> 00:51:04.820
This eloquent man,

00:51:04.820 --> 00:51:05.700
we will send him

00:51:06.500 --> 00:51:09.140
and he will go to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:51:09.140 --> 00:51:10.580
and address him,

00:51:10.580 --> 00:51:11.540
ask him questions

00:51:11.540 --> 00:51:13.380
and offer him whatever he wants

00:51:13.380 --> 00:51:15.460
because they now noticed Islam was growing

00:51:15.460 --> 00:51:16.820
and it was becoming strong.

00:51:16.820 --> 00:51:18.980
Nearly every powerful family

00:51:18.980 --> 00:51:21.140
had some members in it who were Muslim.

00:51:22.020 --> 00:51:24.900
So Utba ibn Rabi'ah was a man who decided,

00:51:24.900 --> 00:51:26.100
okay, I'm going to go.

00:51:26.100 --> 00:51:27.860
He went to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:51:27.860 --> 00:51:28.260
and he says,

00:51:28.260 --> 00:51:30.420
oh, you're a relative of ours.

00:51:30.420 --> 00:51:31.940
You know, we know your status,

00:51:31.940 --> 00:51:33.700
very high standing and so on

00:51:33.700 --> 00:51:36.420
and we'd like you to understand

00:51:36.420 --> 00:51:38.660
that we don't want to be at war, loggerheads.

00:51:38.660 --> 00:51:39.380
What do you want?

00:51:39.380 --> 00:51:40.100
You want wealth?

00:51:40.100 --> 00:51:41.300
We give you wealth.

00:51:41.300 --> 00:51:42.100
You want position?

00:51:42.100 --> 00:51:43.380
We make you our leader.

00:51:43.380 --> 00:51:44.500
You want women?

00:51:44.500 --> 00:51:46.020
You can marry whom you want.

00:51:46.020 --> 00:51:47.860
You want authority?

00:51:47.860 --> 00:51:48.820
We make you the leader

00:51:48.820 --> 00:51:50.020
and you can be in authority.

00:51:50.020 --> 00:51:50.900
What is it that you want?

00:51:50.900 --> 00:51:52.660
You name what you'd like,

00:51:52.660 --> 00:51:53.380
we give it to you.

00:51:54.580 --> 00:51:56.260
And he continued to say,

00:51:56.260 --> 00:51:58.740
but just stop talking about these idols

00:51:58.740 --> 00:52:00.820
and stop talking about this condition of ours.

00:52:00.820 --> 00:52:02.100
We're enjoying life.

00:52:02.100 --> 00:52:04.020
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam told him,

00:52:04.020 --> 00:52:04.980
are you done?

00:52:04.980 --> 00:52:05.860
He says, yes.

00:52:05.860 --> 00:52:06.660
Now listen to me.

00:52:07.300 --> 00:52:09.060
And he began reading verses,

00:52:09.060 --> 00:52:11.940
the opening verses of Surah Fussilat,

00:52:11.940 --> 00:52:13.780
also known as Hameem al-Sajda.

00:52:26.340 --> 00:52:33.700
This man was shocked, gobsmacked,

00:52:33.700 --> 00:52:35.460
listening to these verses,

00:52:35.460 --> 00:52:36.660
powerful verses.

00:52:36.660 --> 00:52:39.060
Let us go home inshallah this evening

00:52:39.060 --> 00:52:41.780
and look up Surah Fussilat

00:52:41.780 --> 00:52:43.460
and check the meanings

00:52:43.460 --> 00:52:46.740
of the first verses of the Surah

00:52:46.740 --> 00:52:48.500
until the verse

00:52:48.500 --> 00:52:51.060
where the punishment of Ad and Thamud

00:52:51.060 --> 00:52:52.580
is made mention of.

00:52:52.580 --> 00:52:54.020
And we will see

00:52:54.020 --> 00:52:56.420
when the Prophet peace be upon him

00:52:56.420 --> 00:52:58.180
got to the verse saying,

00:52:58.180 --> 00:52:59.540
if they turn away,

00:52:59.540 --> 00:53:01.700
warn them of the similar punishment

00:53:01.700 --> 00:53:04.660
that had struck Ad and Thamud before them,

00:53:04.660 --> 00:53:06.820
Utba ibn Rabi'ah took his hand

00:53:06.820 --> 00:53:09.780
and covered the mouth of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:53:09.780 --> 00:53:10.740
and said, stop,

00:53:10.740 --> 00:53:12.100
I don't even want to hear.

00:53:12.100 --> 00:53:13.940
And thereafter he went back to Quraysh

00:53:13.940 --> 00:53:15.460
and told him, I have heard a word

00:53:15.460 --> 00:53:16.420
and I'm telling you

00:53:16.420 --> 00:53:19.460
this word is going to overpower us completely.

00:53:19.460 --> 00:53:20.260
And they looked at him,

00:53:20.260 --> 00:53:21.460
but we sent you to go

00:53:21.460 --> 00:53:22.900
and tell the man something,

00:53:22.900 --> 00:53:24.500
you're coming back telling us something else.

00:53:24.500 --> 00:53:25.460
He says, no, no, no,

00:53:25.460 --> 00:53:26.580
I'm not accepting it,

00:53:26.580 --> 00:53:28.420
but I just want to let you know

00:53:28.420 --> 00:53:29.460
in my view,

00:53:29.460 --> 00:53:31.940
this word is extremely powerful.

00:53:31.940 --> 00:53:35.220
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:53:35.220 --> 00:53:36.900
the ability to understand

00:53:36.900 --> 00:53:38.980
that if the enemies can confirm

00:53:38.980 --> 00:53:40.820
that the word is powerful,

00:53:40.820 --> 00:53:42.900
what about us who are Muslims?

00:53:42.900 --> 00:53:44.260
Have we read it yet?

00:53:44.260 --> 00:53:47.380
This is why I say this evening inshallah,

00:53:47.380 --> 00:53:48.900
let us go back home

00:53:48.900 --> 00:53:50.660
and let us look at the verses

00:53:50.660 --> 00:53:52.020
of Surah Fussilat

00:53:52.100 --> 00:53:54.420
also known as Hameem as-Sajda

00:53:54.420 --> 00:53:55.700
and let us read the meanings

00:53:55.700 --> 00:53:58.260
and see what was said to this man

00:53:58.260 --> 00:54:00.580
Utba ibn Rabi'ah that moved him.

00:54:00.580 --> 00:54:02.660
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala move us

00:54:02.660 --> 00:54:03.860
until we meet again.
